---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Arc^ Framework — Open, humane plasma research" description="Understand the Arc^ Initiative framework: values, principles, licensing expectations, and how students can embed projects in their studies.">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-20">
    <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.4em] text-muted">Framework</p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-semibold">The Arc^ playbook for restorative plasma research</h1>
    <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-muted">
      Arc^ Initiative exists to make plasma-activated water research accessible, ethical, and community governed. We begin with narrative because context matters: who we are, why we share, and how projects stay accountable to people and planet.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 pb-16">
    <div class="grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Pillars</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-muted">
          <li><span class="font-semibold text-white">Open documentation</span> — everything lives in versioned, share-alike MDX so anyone can validate and extend our science.</li>
          <li><span class="font-semibold text-white">Safety-first publishing</span> — risk assessments and human-readable warnings gate every protocol and build.</li>
          <li><span class="font-semibold text-white">Modular ecosystems</span> — projects cascade into sub-studies (e.g., plant species, salinity ranges, instrumentation) so multiple student teams can contribute in parallel.</li>
          <li><span class="font-semibold text-white">Ethical governance</span> — anti-extractive licensing keeps IP in the commons and obliges institutions to return their findings.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-4 rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6 text-sm text-muted">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Roadmap highlights</h3>
        <ol class="list-decimal space-y-3 pl-5">
          <li>Publish foundational narratives and Arc^ Laws.</li>
          <li>Release SALT (saltwater irrigation) MVP documentation and taskboard.</li>
          <li>Launch cross-disciplinary call for honours/PhD partnerships.</li>
          <li>Scale dataset commons and comparative analytics for PAW experiments.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 pb-20">
    <div class="grid gap-12 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Licensing expectations</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-muted">
          Hardware and schematics ship under CERN-OHL-S, software under MIT, documentation under CC BY-SA, and datasets under CC0. Institutions collaborating with Arc^ agree to release derivatives under the same terms and credit the community.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Student integration</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-muted">
          Bring Arc^ into your thesis by introducing your supervisor to our framework, licensing, and safety requirements. Once alignment is confirmed, you’ll join a dedicated project channel and contribute openly to the shared task board.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
